    <string name="accessibility_service_description">
        DeenShield requires the Accessibility Service to power its core features. The service allows the app to:
        \n\n• **See which app you are using:** This is necessary to enforce your App Blocker and Focus Mode rules.
        \n• **Read on-screen content:** This is used by the Keyword Blocker to identify and block unwanted content in real-time.
        \n• **Perform actions:** The service can perform \"back\" or \"home\" gestures to block apps and close distracting content.
        \n\n**Your privacy is our top priority.** All data processing is done entirely on your device. Your on-screen content and app usage are never logged, stored, or shared with us or any third party.
    </string>

